Description: Sherd of East Greek pottery lid or dish with flat-faced rim; fine orange-buff clay; row of regularly set holes through rim, made before firing. Two red-fired bands on rim, asymmetric band on top, and band on underside.
Curator's comments: Typologically close to 1965,0930.521, but in a different clay.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.356)
